article.headline: Bradley 100, Drake 85
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Daniel Ruffin scored 19 points Saturday to leading Bradley to a 100-85 win over Drake. Five players joined Ruffin in double figures for Bradley (17-10, 8-7 Missouri Valley). Zach Andrews scored 18 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, Will Franklin scored 17, and J.J. Tauai and Jeremy Crouch added 12 points apiece. The Braves shot 54 percent from the field, including 14-for-26 from 3-point range. Drake shot 43.8 percent while converting just 6-of-27 from beyond the arc. Ajay Calvin led the Bulldogs (13-13, 4-11) with 19 points. Josh Young chipped in 14 points and seven assists. Bradley led 44-38 at halftime.
